\EMP You know, the girl next door is actually
wearing body paint. She's a total masochist, so
she seems flustered but she's actually getting
excited.

\EMP (N-No one is looking this way, right...?
Please, I beg you, don't notice...!)

\n<Innkeeper>Hmm, it looks like \....\....\.... isn't here
after all... I wonder where they went
\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Are you looking for something? Can I help?
\CE[79]\n<Innkeeper>Oh my, what a surprise! I didn't notice \.!

\n<Innkeeper>I'm sorry, I seem to have lost something
important. But if it's not here, then I must have
dropped it at the Hakudeti...

\n<Innkeeper>Oh dear, just when I thought I could finally open
the room~

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>What did you drop? If it's at Hakudeti, I'm
currently based there, so if you'd like, I can go
and look for it.
\CE[79]\n<Innkeeper>Oh, is that so! That would be incredibly helpful!

\n<Innkeeper>What I dropped was the key to \C[17]the room\C[0].
I went to \C[17]Hakudeti Inn\C[0], where my
brother works, earlier, so I think I probably
dropped it there!

\n<Innkeeper>If you can find the key for me, I promise to lend
you the room. Sorry for the trouble, but please
help me out!

\n<Innkeeper>I think I dropped the key to \C[17]the room\C[0],
probably at \C[17]Hakudeti Inn\C[0]. If you can
find it for me, feel free to use the opened room!
\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Is this the key you were looking for?
\CE[79]\n<Innkeeper>Yes! This is it! You found it for me!

\n<Innkeeper>Oh, I'm so relieved! Changing the key would have
cost me money, and I was wondering what to do.
Thank you so much!

\CE[79]\n<Innkeeper>As promised, please feel free to use that room
over there! You can stay as long as you like, so
make yourself at home!
\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Um, I appreciate it, but are you sure it's okay?

\CE[79]\n<Innkeeper>Well, you know~ \.\. Lately, our place has been
used like a love hotel, so you might be bothered
by the voices around... but if that doesn't bother
you, please feel free to use it

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Thank you very much... In that case, I'll take you
up on your kindness.

The Tachimate Beach Inn can now be used as a base.
You can spend a day here, but please note that the
main scenario will not progress.
\EMP Feel free to use the room whenever you want

\EMP Welcome~ But I'm sorry, we're fully booked
right now.
Which item would you like to confirm?
Regarding the values of desire and reason

About Desire Value and Rationality ValueThese
two values have the characteristic that when one
increases, the other decreases, and together they
function as a Heart Meter.

When the Desire Value exceeds 70%, \C[17]the Lust
Mode\C[0] is activated, and both the meter and
Rain's eyes undergo a change. Although nothing
immediately happens when the mode changes,
\C[17]it has a significant impact on the outcome
of this game.\C[0]

To deactivate the Lust Mode, you need to have a
Rationality Value of 50% or higher.

During the main scenario, there are occasional
scenes where you are prompted to make a Heart
Choice based on the Heart Meter. The range of the
cursor position indicates Rain's emotional state,
and the value of that range increases.

The Desire Value and Rationality Value can also be
increased or decreased through items and events,
in addition to the Heart Choices.

About the Status GaugeIn maps with battles, the
status gauge will be displayed.

When HP reaches 0 in battle, one of the following
will occur: Defeat Event, Return to a specific
location, or Game Over. Game Over only occurs in
certain event battles.

\C[17]TP\C[0] is a very important resource in this
game. In battles, it will mainly be consumed to
use powerful skills, so it's good to always be
aware of the remaining amount.

About Desire ValueWhen the Desire Value
accumulates, it enters a state of Lust, causing
all parameters to decrease slightly. Afterwards,
the Desire Value changes to the Climax Value and
starts accumulating from 0 again.

When \C[17]the Climax Value\C[0] accumulates due
to enemy attacks, it enters a state of
\C[17]Climax\C[0]. When in the state of Climax,
you become unable to take action for several turns
and continue to receive enemy attacks.

After the release of the Climax state, the Climax
Value returns to the Desire Value. The Desire
Value and Climax Value can increase or decrease in
various situations, but outside of battles, they
will never enter the Climax state.

About Equipment DurabilityThe durability of
equipment decreases due to enemy attacks, traps,
and other factors. When it reaches a certain value
or below, the default equipment, the Saint Cross,
will start to deteriorate.

Every time \C[17] is damaged, \C[17]'s defense and
magic defense decrease\C[0], making it easier for
\C[17]'s desire value and climax value to
increase\C[0].

When the equipment durability is low and enters
the Lust state, it can become very disadvantageous
in battle, so it's good to be careful.

About SkillsThere are \C[17] sword techniques,
magic, and blessings\C[0]. \. Sword techniques are
offensive skills, magic is supportive skills such
as self-enhancement and healing, and blessings are
skills with constant effects.

To acquire skills, go to the menu screen -> items
-> important items section and use the \C[17]Holy
Magic Cross Emblem\C[0], then open the \C[17]Skill
Tree\C[0].

On this screen, you can fulfill the conditions set
for each skill (\C[17]Blessing Points\C[0] or
\C[17]Prerequisite Skill\C[0]) and learn new
skills.

About Blessing PointsBlessing Points are the
points required for acquiring \C[17]skills\C[0]
and increasing \C[17]rationality value\C[0]. \.You
can mainly obtain them by clearing events and
missions, as well as defeating enemies.

Once spent, Blessing Points cannot be restored, so
please carefully decide when to consume them.

About Events and MissionsWhen you talk to the
townspeople with a mark, events and missions will
occur.

Events are generally completed by viewing
conversations. In many cases, it will involve
accumulating some kind of sexual experience or
level of lewdness. Additionally, there are often
opportunities to earn blessing points.

Missions are completed by achieving certain
objectives. You can check the details of the
missions from the Mission section in the menu.

By completing missions, you will receive rewards
and blessing points. However, unlike events, it
does not involve accumulating sexual experience or
lewdness.

The map has \C[17]day and night\C[0]. You can pass
time by sleeping in the guards' barracks.

Depending on the day and night, different events
and missions occur, so exploring each of them may
lead to new discoveries.

About Desire LockBy fulfilling certain
conditions, Rain's desire known as Desire Lock
will be unlocked.

To unlock it, there are various conditions, but
the most common one is the number of times you
have had \C[17]sexual experiences\C[0]. It will be
automatically unlocked by fulfilling certain
sexual experiences beyond a certain threshold.

You can check the Desire Lock and sexual
experiences from the 'Desire Lock' section in the
menu. Additionally, by selecting a unlocked Desire
Lock, you can confirm the unlocking conditions.

By unlocking the Desire Lock, you will be able to
see events that you couldn't see before, and you
will gain new abilities such as being able to go
out in specific outfits.

To acquire the 'Blessing Points' necessary for
Rain to obtain skills, it is most common to obtain
them through events. So, if you want to strengthen
Rain, it might be a good idea to aim for unlocking
Desire Lock.
